x4freetext: A solid angle of 0.8 msr was used for all
the measurements. Momentum spectra of the 3He particles
were detected by a multi-wire gas proportional chamber
with delay-line read-out which used drift-time
information to interpolate between anode wires. The
counter was mounted in the focal plane of the
spectrometer and its position-sensitive area was 800
mm*72 mm. A 5 mm thick plastic scintillation counter,
behind the focal plane, was used for particle
identification.
A self-supporting 740 mu-g/cm2 thick nickel target
enriched to 99.8% in 58Ni. The thickness of the target
was determined by weighing and also by measuring the
energy loss of 5.802 MeV a-particles from a 244Cm
source. The difference between these two measurements
was about 10% and the average of the two results was
used for determination of the absolute cross section.
High-resolution energy spectra and relative
cross sections were measured using a thin (140
mu-g/cm2) nickel target, obtained by evaporation of
enriched (99.8%) 58Ni material onto a 10 mu-g/cm2 thick
carbon backing.
